Certainly! You can use the following JavaScript function to convert a number from base 10 to base 8:

```javascript
function convertBase10ToBase8(number) {
    if (typeof number !== 'number' || number < 0) {
        throw new Error('Please provide a non-negative integer.');
    }

    return number.toString(8);
}

// Example usage:
const base10Number = 64;
const base8Number = convertBase10ToBase8(base10Number);
console.log(`Base 10: ${base10Number}, Base 8: ${base8Number}`);
```

In this function, `toString(8)` is used to convert the base 10 number to base 8. It will return a string representation of the number in base 8. The function also includes a simple check to ensure the input is a non-negative integer. You can remove or modify the check according to your requirements.
